            <title>[AMQ-6378] KahaDb recover from corrupt metadata state locations that can be rebuilt</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-6378</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The index tracks producerAudit and ackMessageFileMap locations. Failure to recreate/read on startup can be replayed from the journal however if the locations are corrupt the broker errors out. In this case a replay can still recreate this information.&lt;/p&gt;

